 appreciate your attitude and would gladly go over the story with you. If it is not too much trouble for you to come to Boston, it would be a great help, since I have had to go away on a trip a week ago and a repeated absence would be difficult to organize. It is extremely kind of you to suggest your coming here.

Very sincerely yours,

V. Nabokov2





TO: MRS. DOUGLAS HORTON

CC, 1 p.

Cambridge, Mass.





November 30, 1947

